## Stickers balance
> Request example

```shell
curl 'https://<%= config[:api_endpoint] %>/loyalty/stickers/balance?shop_id=SHOP_ID&shop_secret=SHOP_SECRET&identifier=PHONE'
```

> The above command returns JSON structured like this:

```json
[
  {
    "campaign_id": 113,
    "campaign_code": "...",
    "campaign_name": "...",
    "campaign_status": "...",
    "amount": 13
  },
  {
    "campaign_id": 2,
    "campaign_code": "...",
    "campaign_name": "...",
    "campaign_status": "...",
    "amount": 24
  },
  ...
]
```

Method returns member's stickers balance

### HTTP Request

`GET https://<%= config[:api_endpoint] %>/loyalty/stickers/balance`

### Query Parameters

| Parameter   | Required | Description               |
|-------------|----------|---------------------------|
| shop_id     | true     | Your API key              |
| shop_secret | true     | Your API secret key       |
| identifier  | true     | User's phone (identifier) |





